#: ../../SO1.md:927
msgid "National parks and nature reserves may be expected to show increasing land productivity over time. However, the situation may often be more complex depending on the ecological   status and type of management practiced in each park. Therefore, it is crucial for experts to identify specific national protected areas where recovery is expected over the period covered by the LPD map. To support this verification, global datasets such as the World Database on Protected Areas (WDPA) can be used."
